\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Ayram\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s words were heavy with righteous indignation, as if he were accusing Mandri of some lack of filial devotion. Unfortunately for him, Mandri was an old hand at shirking duties. Not that he believed any of this Amalgamete nonsense anyways. If there was a demon anywhere, it was surely inside Ayram, stretching his limbs and deepening his voice . He was unnatural.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93As I said, in exchange for my freedom, I\u8217\'92ll kill whatever you want.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93In exchange\u8230\'85\u8221\'94 Ayram repeated in disbelief. \u8220\'93This is useless. He simply doesn\u8217\'92t know.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You would be correct,\u8221\'94 Mandri, fearing an opportunity was slipping away. \u8220\'93But look. Say I kill your greatest enemy\u8230\'85now you\u8217\'92ve got a new greatest enemy, don\u8217\'92t you? When will it stop? That\u8217\'92s what I\u8217\'92m worried about. If I had my own bright Spark, then my body and my will would be my own and I could walk away and leave the world in peace.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Ayram\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s brow jumped into an incredulous arc. \u8220\'93You want me to forge you a Divine Spark? I\u8217\'92ve been mistaken for a god before, but never Solraheen Himself!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93A Spark was stolen from me. Could one not be returned in a similar way?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 All eyes turned to the scarecrow witch, Elrahet. Naturally, the mysteries of the Spark were her domain. But she simply shook her head and stated, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93A Spark stolen can never be returned.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Then it can\u8217\'92t be done,\u8221\'94 said Ayram firmly.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I did not say }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 that}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 ,\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 Elrahet snipped as her hand twisted tight on the knobby head of her sand-smoothed cane. To Mandri\u8217\'92s great surprise, she even savored a sneer at her leader. \u8220\'93Yet still, a Mazid is a kind of creature for which no true Spark exists. Giving it one would require a sacrifice greater than any. Better to wring the will out of the boy. The girl }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 will}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  wring it out of him.\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
